</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3275FF9F83A0FEA82D95FE4E" author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[222,446,366,393]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93275FF9F823FFEA82D58FE4E" box="[321,371,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Variation in fundamental number, with 72 and 76, was reported due to a pericentric inversion affecting one medium and one small autosomal pair (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3275FF9F8042FE542FDCFE6A" author="Lima, J. F. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S." box="[828,1015,403,429]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref68699" refString="Lima, J. F. S., Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S. (2003) A new karyotype of Oligoryzomys (Sigmodontinae, Rodentia) from central Brazil. Hereditas, 139, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.2003.01706. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Lima 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93275FF9F8001FE542F84FE6A" box="[895,943,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3275FF9F877CFE5428F4FE6A" author="Di-Nizo, C. B. &amp; Ventura, K. &amp; Ferguson-Smith, M. A. &amp; O'Brien, P. C. M. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J." box="[1026,1247,402,429]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="0117579" refId="ref66405" refString="Di-Nizo, C. B., Ventura, K., Ferguson-Smith, M. A., O'Brien, P. C. M., Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. &amp; Silva, M. J. J. (2015) Comparative chromosome painting in six species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia, Sigmodontinae) and the karyotype evolution of the genus. Public Library of Science one, 10 (2), e 0117579. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0117579" type="journal article" year="2015">
Di-Nizo 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93275FF9F871AFE5428BEFE6A" box="[1124,1173,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). These variation in fundamental number occurs sympatrically on specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193275FF9F80CAFE702FDEFE16" box="[948,1013,439,465]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Goiás</collectingRegion>
(FN = 72 and FN = 74) and 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193275FF9F864EFE7029B7FE16" box="[1328,1436,439,465]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
(FN = 74 and FN = 76), states of 
<collectingCountry id="F31B766B3275FF9F816DFE1C2E7CFE32" box="[531,599,475,501]" name="Brazil" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation id="C68E03403275FF9F8119FE1C2E95FE32" box="[615,702,475,501]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="62.[151,239,502,528]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="TABLE 9. Karyotype data of genus Oligoryzomys. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection localities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Table 9</tableCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13372A7E3275FF9F81B5FE1C2F35FE32" box="[715,798,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1098,1122]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,187,1067]" captionTargetId="figure-17@59.[151,1436,181,1073]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 17. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Oligoryzomys. (r) O. mattogrossae; (■) O. microtis; (○) O. moojeni; (☆) O. rupestris; (▲) O. stramineus; (l) O. utiaritensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423661" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423661/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). C-banding metaphases exhibited blocks of constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region of almost all autosomal pairs. The X chromosome C-band encompasses from the pericentromeric region to the short arm almost entirely heterochromatic. The medium subtelocentric Y chromosome was entirely heterochromatic (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3275FF9F81DAFD802826FDA6" author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[676,1037,583,609]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93275FF9F80FCFD802F9EFDA6" box="[898,949,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3275FF9F8767FD8028F7FDA6" author="Lima, J. F. S. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S." box="[1049,1244,583,609]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref68699" refString="Lima, J. F. S., Bonvicino, C. R. &amp; Kasahara, S. (2003) A new karyotype of Oligoryzomys (Sigmodontinae, Rodentia) from central Brazil. Hereditas, 139, 1 - 6. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1601 - 5223.2003.01706. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Lima 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93275FF9F8723FD8028BBFDA6" box="[1117,1168,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). G-banding was also performed (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3275FF9F822FFDAC2E93FD42" author="Andrades-Miranda, J. &amp; Oliveira, L. F. B. &amp; Lima-Rosa, C. A. &amp; Nunes, A. P. &amp; Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S." box="[337,696,619,645]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="1080 - 1091" refId="ref63690" refString="Andrades-Miranda, J., Oliveira, L. F. B., Lima-Rosa, C. A., Nunes, A. P., Zanchin, N. I. T. &amp; Mattevi, M. S. (2001 a) Chromosome studies of seven species of Oligoryzomys (Rodentia: Sigmodontinae) from Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy, 82, 1080 - 1091. https: // doi. org / 10.1644 / 1545 - 1542 (2001) 082 % 3 C 1080: CSOSSO % 3 E 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2001">
Andrades-Miranda 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93275FF9F8151FDAC2E4AFD42" box="[559,609,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2001a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
